summary: The All Blacks are set to face Japan in a one-off Test in Yokohama. The All Blacks are expected to crush Japan and kick off their year-end tour in style. However, Japan has proven to be a tough opponent in the past, and the All Blacks will need to be at their best to avoid an upset. New Zealand has named its team for the match, and the All Blacks are starting to change the game. Scott Robertson is the head coach of the All Blacks, and he is known for his innovative approach to the game. The All Blacks have a number of new players in their squad, and they are eager to make an impression. One of the new players is rookie Braydon Ennor, who is "gutted" to be making his Test debut against Japan. The All Blacks are confident that they can beat Japan, but they are also aware of the challenge that they face. Sir Wayne Smith, the All Blacks assistant coach, said that the team is "not copiers" and that they are always looking to improve. The All Blacks will be looking to put on a show against Japan, and they will be confident of getting the win.
